description: After being zapped by Penguin's Songinator ray, the Batwheels find themselves only able to communicate through song! They'll need to learn to harmonize as a team to defeat the musical prankster.

title: Percy in the Middle
description: After Gordon tells all the young engines that they have a day off to relax, Thomas and Diesel insist on a teamed relay race through the obstacle course. Percy is the only one who isn't interested in playing, so Thomas asks him to referee instead. He reluctantly agrees and the race is on! Coming to a split second finish, Percy determines Thomas' team wins, but Diesel doesn't accept and calls for a rematch. Once again the teams race and Diesel wins after accidentally causing an oil spill. Both teams become so angry with each other, they're too distracted when Percy runs off to chase butterflies. Thomas, Diesel, and friends finally notice Percy's absence and speed after him, but they'll need to learn their lesson about sportsmanship if they want to ensure this day off is a success.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Halloween Song
description: A special animated music video episode to the tune of Blippi's new "Halloween Song"

title: Bam's Clawful Mistake
description: Bam brings Catwoman's Catmobile, Kitty, to life so the Batwheels can have even teams for their game of "Bat-Ball," but the Kitty "Kitty" is too wild to be contained, despite Bam's best attempts to convince her to play along.

title: The Light in the Forest
description: Cheer bonds with a migrating firefly-like creature, called a Sparklewing, who stows aboard the Cloudseeker. The two become good friends, but there's a problem: Sparklewings must finish their migration to bring life-giving nutrients to the fields of the Silver Lining. Cheer's difficult and emotional parting with her new friend is only possible once they both accept that it's for a greater good.

title: Underwater Star
description: Moxie Manatee hires The Looney Builders to build an obstacle course for the Sandy Shells Preschool Games, but Lola isn't listening to her crew.

title: Batty Kathy
description: As The Looney Builders build Kathy Bat an upside-down radio station, Porky has concerns but doesn't speak up.

title: Toothbrush
description: Brush every day and keep the dentist away! A night adventure into a sleeping mouth has Blippi inspecting some teeth. Teeth that are in need of a clean! It's a good thing Bill Brushy is on the case and with his toothpaste and bristles he shows Blippi just how to get the perfect clean!

title: 10 Little Buses
description: It's a sunny day and Ella is having fun drawing pictures of the buses of Lellobee City Farm! Help Ella count all of the buses as they drive by!

title: Looney Science
description: The Looney Builders build a science museum in the desert where Wile E. Coyote becomes distracted by the Road Runner.

title: Accidents Happen Boo Boo Song
description: Ella falls over, but Heidi the Horse teaches her to get right back up again!

title: Ace in the Hole
description: When a group of alley dogs, aided by a heroic stray, are saved from Catwoman by kind-hearted Buff, he brings them all back to live in the Batcave, unbeknownst to the rest of the Bat-Family.

title: Festival of Hearts
description: When two greedy gnomes steal Love-a-Lot's gift-making crystal heart, the Care Bears must get it back in time for the Festival of Hearts that they are holding for the Whiffles. In doing so, they have to teach the gnomes the meaning of caring.

title: The Treasure of Treetop Woods/Zee Makes an Amazing Maze!
description: Ranger Nat's hike turns to adventure when he finds a treasure map. The only problem is that he can't read it./Zee and MacBarm are setting up their corn maze with the help of Zee's Zee Mobile… that is, until it breaks down inside the maze.

title: Road Trip
description: On a mission to a remote area of the Silver Lining, Cheer questions the directions from Bedtime's maps. Everyone else backs Bedtime: he's never been wrong before! When the directions turn out to be wrong and lead them into danger, Cheer must trust her instincts to find a way out of the mess.

title: Mechanic Panic
description: When Jestah injures herself preparing for an extreme sports competition with the other Zoomers, Bibi helps her overcome her fear of going to the mechanic so she can heal up in time to compete.

title: Blue Engine Blues
description: After getting through a rough night's sleep and finding out his beach day gets cancelled due to the rain, Thomas winds up in the grumpiest of moods. Encountering Riff and Jiff with their usual happy-go-lucky attitudes, Thomas comes to the conclusion that he'll only be liked when he appears happy. He puts on fake smile for the rest of the day, but his words don't match his demeanor and everyone can see right through him. Finally, Thomas comes across Riff and Jiff again, who reveal they're also upset about the cruddy day! They teach him that nobody can be happy all the time, and sometimes you need a friend to vent to on the days you're most blue.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: On the Trail of the Cloud Bouncer
description: When spores from a strange plant take over control of the Cloudseeker, Cheer and the team must risk losing the vehicle - their home away from home and their only way back to Care-A-Lot - in order to save the Whiffles' newly-planted valley.

title: Bear Hibernation
description: Blippi wonders how do bears prepare for hibernation?

title: Honey
description: Blippi and FETCH shrink down and fly inside a very active beehive, where they meet Bijon, the fast-talking, fast-moving Worker Bee. With a talent for rhyming and making honey, Bijon rhymes her way through the sweet explanation of how delicious honey is made. What a very buzzy... erm...busy day!

title: Thomas for a Day
description: It's a blustery day on Sodor and Percy finds that his preferred route is closed! He must journey into Crumble Canyon -- a place that makes him terribly nervous! But before he can face his fears, Diesel blasts by, bonking his cargo of blue paint all over the jittery mail engine! Percy is unrecognizable as himself -- instead, he looks just like Thomas! His impromptu makeover inspires Percy to be brave just like his best loco-migo -- and pretend to be the Number One Engine for the day! When Whiff loses his glasses, Percy escorts him across the island and learns that the bravery isn't in the blue paint -- it's inside him!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Heads Shoulders Knees and Toes
description: It's animal bath time at the farm! With a fun twist on the traditional lyrics of 'Head and Shoulders, Knees and Toes', Ella and Rishi wash the "Mane, Muzzle, Back and Hooves" of Heidi the horse, Pablo the pig and Mama Duck. It's time to get scrubbing!

title: Pop a Wheelie
description: Thomas and Diesel take a friendly competition too far and put an important delivery rescue at risk as they race across Sodor.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Bubbles
description: Blippi wonders how do you make bubbles?

title: Trick or Treat
description: D.BO wonders what is trick-or-treating?

title: Holiday Party
description: "Lighting up the farm for a big 'festive' celebration Lots of lights around the farm and decorations from different cultures"

title: Blippi Saves Christmas
description: Blippi wonders how does Santa know where we live?

title: Wheels On The Bus
description: Ella, Mei and Carlos travel around Lellobee City on a bus delivering fresh farm produce to their friends.

title: Sorry Not Sorry
description: While observing an ancient Whiffle ritual, Grumpy accidentally steps on a sentient plant. When his apology sends the plant and Whiffles into an upset, Share helps him learn how to genuinely apologize from his heart, and that a real apology is about how the other person feels, not about yourself.

title: Ride Along
description: After Kitty the Catmobile saves Bam when he's in a tight spot, Bam decides to take her on a ride along patrol in the hopes of recruiting her as a Batwheel if he can convince her to stop playing long enough to focus on their mission!

title: Halloween Party
description: D.BO wonders how do you throw the best Halloween party ever?

title: Guitar
description: Blippi wonders how does a guitar work?

title: Squirrels
description: Blippi and FETCH are going on a treasure hunt! For Squirrel treasure that is. Their new friend Sparky the Squirrel has her nuts buried all over the park and Blippi tries to remember where she buried them. Sparky remembers them all though and Blippi learns why squirrels bury their nuts.

title: Recycle Stomp
description: Mei, the children and some animals are in the park collecting trash to recycle!

title: More Cowbell
description: Thomas is elated when he finds a cowbell on the side of the tracks, until his friends start hogging it.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Dim Sum
description: Chef Poyung Panda hires The Looney Builders to build her a Dim Sum bus in China. The crew faces a major setback and Bugs worries about letting down his favorite chef.

title: Up in the Air
description: After he causes the Batwing to crash, Bam becomes obsessed with making it up to her during a high-stakes aerial mission against Penguin and his giant ducky blimp.

title: Whistle Woes
description: When Thomas's whistle suddenly stops working, he learns that he doesn't need his whistle to still be himself.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Bats
description: Can you see in the dark? Blippi can't either! But on this adventure Blippi and FETCH fly around in the dark with Matt the Bat who shows them how he uses echolocation to see and hear in the dark! Who needs eyes when you can use echo-echo-echoes?

title: Rules of the Game
description: When Thomas builds an obstacle course for his friends, he gets upset when they won't play with it HIS way.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Things That Go Plunk
description: A shy, puny member of the Bad Crowd shows up at the Cloudseeker claiming he's been kicked out of Blusterland for being nice. The Bears, leery at first, take him in despite Grumpy's suspicions that he is in cahoots with Bluster. It appears Grumpy is right - but thanks to the Care Bears, the little guy turns into a good friend with the courage to thwart Bluster's latest scheme.

title: Chasing Rainbows
description: Thomas and Kana journey across Sodor to find the prize at the end of a rainbow.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Super Screen Cleaners
description: Thomas pretends to be a hero to help ensure the movie screen Nia's delivering arrives clean and pristine.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Ghost Train
description: Percy has to deliver the mail on Halloween when everyone knows the legendary Ghost Train comes out! Thomas rolls along to help Percy face his fears, but when a "real" Ghost Train appears... things get almost spooky.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Mountain
description: Blippi and TABBS head off on an icy adventure and fly up the side of Mt. Everest, the world's tallest mountain! They are joined by Betty the Yeti who is climbing to the top of the mountain in search of the ultimate snack - fresh snow!

title: Magnet Mayhem/Stop That Train
description: The magnet crane at the construction site accidentally turns on, sucking up all the metal, including the Mecha Builders!/Roof is delivering eggs to Marwyn at the Train Station, that is, until the train pulls into the station and can't stop!

title: Capture the Flag
description: When Percy loses Nia's parade flag before the big parade, Thomas helps them search for it before the event begins.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Buff's BFF
description: When Buff befriends Mr. Freeze's snowcrawler Snowy, the other Batwheels bristle at the thought of hanging out with a "bad guy…" so Buff sets out to change their minds.

title: Tunnel Troubles
description: Sir Topham Hatt has two exciting announcements: it is time for the beautiful Butterfly Migration AND there is a new unnamed express tunnel ready for the first engine to pass through! Thomas and Diesel ask Sir Topham Hatt to hold a race where the winner's name will become the official name of the new tunnel. When both ambitious engines get stuck in the tunnel during the race, they stubbornly refuse to move... even if it risks missing the Butterfly Migration with their friends!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Garbage Truck
description: Blippi and TABBS shrink down and fly into a garbage truck where they meet Horace, a singing and dancing fly, who shows them what he loves to eat--garbage!

title: Bath Song
description: Ella gets covered in mud so she goes into Mei's farmhouse to have a bath.

title: Taz in Toyland/Born to Sing (song)/A Secret Tweet
description: Taz in Toyland: After Taz breaks all of his toys, Granny gives him one last chance to care for something./A Secret Tweet: The babies plan a surprise birthday party for Tweety.

title: Nia's Perfect Plan
description: Nia has volunteered for a big day of deliveries and is determined to make the perfect plan to get it done, but when things start to go awry, she doggedly sticks to her plan and refuses any help.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

title: Snowy Excavator Song
description: A special animated music video episode to the tune of Blippi's new "Snowy Excavator" Song.

title: A Wide Delivery
description: When the trains must deliver in pairs, Thomas is disappointed to be paired with Diesel instead of his BFF Percy.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Can't Stop the Martians/Best Nest Test
description: The Martians come to Pretty Big City but find themselves in need of help when they are unable to land their spaceship./Zee needs to communicate with Sif in outer space but can't because a bird has made its home on top of the satellite dish!

title: Tyrannosaurus Wrecks
description: Thomas and the other Engines get to deliver some newly discovered dinosaur bones, but they must deliver them in the correct order for assembly, which isn't as easy as it sounds...
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Sandcastle
description: Blippi and TABBS go to the beach, where they meet Crabby the Crab! A local expert on sandcastles, Crabby teaches them how to build a castle that can't get washed away!

title: Hide and Surprise!
description: While playing hide and seek with Percy, Diesel accidentally gets stranded on a barge that floats out to sea, where it becomes a group effort to rescue him.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: New Cat in Town/Baby Bunny (song)/The Magic of Spring
description: New Cat in Town: Sylvester is jealous of the attention baby Pepe is receiving./The Magic of Spring: Bugs' failure as a magician turns to success when he experiences the true magic of nature.

title: Neon Beach Party
description: Bluster and his Bad Crowd arrive at a lakeside beach for his summer vacation, unaware that the Care Bears are having their vacation on the opposite shore. Trapped inside Bluster's climate-control dome and forced to spend their vacations together, the Bears must find a way to make friends with their ill-tempered neighbors.

title: Tri-and-a-Half-a-lon
description: The engines are revved up for their homemade obstacle course event known as the Tri-and-a-half-a-lon. During practice, Nia worries that she's never been able to beat the timer, but Sandy and Carly encourage her to keep practicing before the event the next day. Nia becomes so committed that she overworks herself, zooming all over the island well into the night. The morning of the event, Nia finds she's so tired she isn't sure if she can race, but she pushes through, learning that while practice is good, too much practice can wear you out so much that you miss the fun.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Nia's Balloon Blunder
description: When a parade balloon Nia is set to deliver flies away, Thomas helps Nia adjust her plans to get it back.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Letting Off Steam
description: When Thomas and Percy get into their first big fight they're afraid that their friendship is over... until Nia helps them figure out how to resolve it.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: The Ultimate Bad Seed
description: Malcom becomes the new boss of Blusterland when he tricks Bluster into letting him transfer his inner-badness into a Bad Seed, leaving Bluster a polite shell of his former self. To neutralize the dangerous Seed before Malcom can use it to turn the Silver Lining into a giant Blusterland, the Care Bears must transfer its bad energy back into the only thing that can hold it, Bluster himself!

title: Back To School
description: Ella creates a school set up at the farm and teaches her animal friends what school is all about!

title: Hot Air Percy
description: Thomas and Percy are excited to deliver a special balloon for the hot-air balloon festival, but the balloon is wrapped up tight. They're instructed not to peek at it until they arrive. While making the delivery, part of the balloon pops out of its tarp and the wind carries it skyward, along with Percy. Percy never expected to enjoy a flight that much! Now it's up to Thomas to get help from Harold and Beresford in order to bring Percy home.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Catwalk
description: The Looney Builders are hired by Penelope Pussycat to build a fashion runway in France where they are encouraged to make their design bigger and more fun.

title: After the Klatternack
description: The Care Bears try to capture the Klatternack, a comical creature whose non-stop nonsense is annoying the local Whiffles. The Bears are joined by the ultra-serious Tracker, who has long been after the Klatternack himself. But despite their combined efforts, the wily creature continues to elude them - until Share realizes there is more going on than meets the eye.

title: License to Joke
description: When Redbird tries his hand at espionage as "V-8, the Super-Spy", he quickly realizes he's gotten in over his head, so Redbird teams up with Bibi to save the Amusement Mile from Dr. Spy!

title: Ella's Campfire Sing-A-Long
description: Ella has her first camping experience. It's time to gather round the fire for a special sing-a-long.

title: One Wise Bear
description: The Bears become lost in the Valley of Whispering Winds, where voices whisper in their ears and make them lose faith in themselves. Racing to their rescue, Tenderheart leads them to the only one who knows the antidote to the words of the Winds: a mysterious old bear of great wisdom who teaches them a valuable lesson about listening to your heart.

title: Old Macdonald
description: Ella and Bee play a game of hide and seek on the farm with Carlos, Pablo, Lettie and Heidi.

title: Skate Park
description: The Looney Builders build a skate park for the kids, but it soon interferes with Hoots Talon and his friends' activities.

title: Batty Body Swap
description: After agreeing to swap motherboards and change bodies, the Batwheels have to quickly learn to "drive a mile in each other's wheels" in time to stop the approaching Legion of Zoom!

title: Funshine's Un-fun Day
description: Funshine can't bring himself to tell Cheer he accidentally broke her beloved necklace. His attempts to repair the broken necklace end in failure, so he hides it. When Cheer wrongly thinks Dibble is responsible for the disappearance of the necklace, Funshine knows he must tell her the truth.

title: A Lot Like Lola/Baby Elmer Had a Friend (song)/Mother's Day Madness
description: A Lot Like Lola: Lola wants everyone to be more like her until they all start acting exactly like her./Mother's Day Madness: The babies compete to see who can create the best Mother's Day card.

title: Hair Cut-Ups/Does Your Tongue Hang Low (song)/A Clean Sweep
description: Hair Cut-Ups: Lola is afraid of getting her first haircut./A Clean Sweep: Daffy tries to avoid cleaning up by sweeping his toys under a rug.

title: Speedster Sandy
description: After yet another victorious race, Kana seems unbeatable! No engine on the island is as fast as Kana! However, this does not stop Sandy from challenging the electric engine. Everyone is sure Kana will win again. Sandy picks the route for the race, using her smarts and her small stature to her advantage! By focusing on her own strengths rather than comparing to Kana's strengths, she makes a fast track to victory!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: The Team Work song
description: Join Ella, Rishi, Heidi, and Bingo in their teamwork making the farm more beautiful and tidy. Working as a team, they do some weeding, they paint the fence and they put some rubbish back into an overturned bin. Soon, the front of the farm is looking neat and they made it work together!

title: Melissa the Hero/My Bunny Lies over the Ocean (song)/The Trouble with Larry
description: Melissa the Hero: Melissa brags about helping Petunia to the point of self-aggrandizement./The Trouble with Larry: Petunia invents an imaginary friend to help her always get her way.

title: No Monsters Scared of the Dark
description: The Baby Pumpkins are scared of the dark as they go to the halloween party!

title: Splash Zone
description: Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a giant water slide for Looneyburg's waterpark. He keeps adding onto the design with the support of Bugs until problems arise.

title: The Big Whifflesnooze
description: Cheer, distracted by other work, doesn't give her complete attention to a problem with the Whiffles. The mistake starts a chain of comical events that results in the Whiffles going into a one-hundred-year sleep that can only be rectified by an ancient chant.

title: Glow Toy
description: When Jessica can't get a new toy to work, she learns a new way to appreciate it.

title: L-L-Lellogames
description: Mei has set up an obstacle course for Ella and friends that turns farmyard chores into a fun game!

title: Bee a Bee dance
description: Come sing this song and dance with our Lellobee City Farm friends to learn how to move like a Bee! Ella, Izzy, and Lettie are having fun playing and learning about bees!

title: Loose Change/Oh Where, Oh Where Has My Baby Martian Gone (song)/Act Your Age
description: Loose Change: Sylvester is upset when Granny paints the bedroom but he learns the importance of change./Act Your Age: The kids try to see who can act most like a baby, while vying for Granny's attention.

title: The Legend of Jack O'Lantern/The Mecha T-Rex
description: It's Halloween and everything is set for the Zee Mobile to pull the haunted hayride… until it drives away./Timmy can't wait to trick or treat as a Mecha T-Rex, but his Halloween is almost ruined when he can't reach the arms to his costume.

title: Waffle Cones for Whiffles
description: The Whiffles are too hot and tired to work because their daily treat, colorful ice in Waffles Cones delivered by the whimsical "Icelings," hasn't arrived - the Icelings have mysteriously disappeared. As the Care Bears search for them, Share volunteers to make the treats. It's much more than she can handle but she's determined to go-it-alone and not ask for help. Things get out of hand and Share ends up snared in Bluster's trap with the Icelings, who help her to realize that we get more done when we work together.

title: The Case of the Missing Crystal Pinecone/The Pretty Big Thing
description: Izzy and Timmy go to dig up treasure at the top of Lawrence Pinecone's Statue's shadow… only to find that nothing's there!/The mysterious "Pretty Big Thing" is scaring the people of Pretty Big City from going to work… but what is it?

title: Father's Day
description: It's Father's Day and to celebrate there's BBQ at the farm. Ben and Izzy are there with their Dads. Ella's Dad can't attend, but that doesn't stop Ella joining in with all the fun.

title: Present Tense/The Hare Hid Under the Fountain (song)/The Neat and the Sloppy
description: Present Tense: The Baby Looney Tunes pitch in to make an Arbor Day gift for Granny while Baby Lola, who suggested they do so, tries to make Granny a present on her own./The Neat and the Sloppy: A study in contrasts enlivens this odd couple's antics. Baby Daffy is the compulsive mess maker, and Baby Sylvester is the cleanliness freak.

title: Sheep Shenanigans
description: When passing through the snowy pastures of Sodor, Thomas, Percy, and Diesel find an adorable sheep all by herself. When the sheep takes a liking to Diesel, the three engines decide to let her sleep with them in the sheds until they can find out where she came from. However, when the sheep's fluffy herd arrives for an extended sheep-over, the engines realize that their fleecy and noisy guests have overstayed their welcome. Will they be able to get the sheep back home where they came from, or will the baaa-ing sheep continue to disrupt the engines' sleep?
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: It All Adds Up
description: It is a special day for Harold -- the Northern Lights will shimmer over Sodor at sunset! He cannot wait to share this moment with his engine friends on Lookout Mountain. However, Thomas and the gang have a busy day ahead of them, which is impacted by damage to the Sodor Suspension Bridge. Carly and Sandy warn the excited engines that they should only cross the bridge in case of an emergency -- a rule that is ignored by Kana, Diesel, Nia, AND Thomas! When the bridge finally collapses and prevents them from reaching Lookout Mountain in time, Harold selflessly chooses to help his friends instead of see the Lights. His sacrifice teaches the young engines an important lesson: your actions add up - stay away until it is safe to play.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: For Whom the Toll Calls/John Jacob Jongle Elmer Fudd (song)/Cereal Boxing
description: For Whom the Toll Calls: Petunia and Tweety learn how to call long distance and amass a huge phone bill./Cereal Boxing: The kids become obsessed with getting the prizes from boxes of sugary cereal.

title: Flush Hour/Paws and Feathers (song)/I Strain
description: Flush Hour: The babies learn the purpose of toilets./I Strain: Petunia gets hooked on watching television and stops playing with her friends.

title: Wonderful World
description: Nia shows Thomas and Diesel how much unique beauty exists in Sodor, which comes in handy when they need plants to beautify a Plaza in Vicarstown.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Mission: Stuffed Animal
description: When Redbird takes one of Buff's stuffed animals without asking and it accidentally gets swiped by the Legion of Zoom, Red enlists Bam to help him make a daring rescue.

title: Fruity Ice Cream
description: It's a hot day so Woolly Sheep sets up an ice cream stall outside Lellobee City Farm. Ella, Rishi, Lettie and Carlos bring Woolly fresh apples, oranges, bananas and cherries from the farm so Woolly can make them delicious and refreshing fruity ice cream.

title: Can-Do Submarine Crew
description: Thomas and Percy think they're great communicators, but when they're tasked with delivering a submarine to Vicarstown, communication becomes a bit more difficult… to say the least!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: The Great Giggle
description: The Care Bears are to witness the annual blooming of the Pinata Tree, an ancient event that can only happen if the Keeper of the Tree sees something that makes him giggle. Good Luck's giggle-inducing entertainment act goes awry because he relies on his errant lucky shamrock for success. He must learn to forgo luck and practice his act instead.

title: Dynamic Du-Oh-No
description: When Snowy and Jestah team up to execute a mysterious plan involving rare freeze-berries, Batwing and Buff pair up to take on the dastardly duo, but Batwing decides to carry out the mission herself, putting both her and Buff at risk.

title: Moo-ving Day!/Follow That Breeze
description: Zee's growth ray turns Moobert giant, but when a storm rolls in, the Mechas need to build a shelter big enough to fit her./After Ranger Nat's kite blows away in the wind, the Mechas and Timmy learn to build their own kite to find it.

title: Riddle Me This
description: After struggling to solve a riddle from Riddler's helicopter Quizz, Redbird must learn to speak up and share his ideas with the Batwheels if they hope to figure out the villain's true scheme.

title: Ducks
description: Blippi gets up close and personal with Declan the Duck in his quest to find how ducks float! Under the water, above the water, through feather tunnels and tooting air bubbles, Blippi and Declan work together to discover the answer.

title: Keep Calm and Roll On
description: After Jestah's insults get the best of her, a short-tempered Bibi tries to not let the big-wheeled bully's words get to her so she can help Batgirl catch Harley.

title: Mr. McStuffles/Twinkle, Baby Looney Star (song)/Picture This!
description: Mr. McStuffles: Daffy doesn't want to give up his old toy, even after he's outgrown it./Picture This: The babies create their own endings to fairytales.

title: Roller Coasting
description: Thomas wants to show Percy what it's like to ride a roller coaster, so Thomas turns the tracks of Sodor into a thrill ride.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: A Jet Out of Water
description: After refusing to practice with her new underwater mode, Batwing is unable to save Batman from Penguin's sunken ship trap. The Batwheels must help Wing practice her submersible skills before she can save the day.

title: Old Macdonald
description: Rishi goes around the farm with Ella, organising all the animals so they can have a soccer game!

title: Twinkle Twinkle
description: Bee gets one of Ella's glow in the dark stars stuck on their tummy and amazes the animals.

title: Nocturnal Animals
description: Blippi wonders why do some animals come out at night?

title: Cheddar Days
description: The Mouse Sisters hire The Looney Builders to build a cheese café featuring a mural by Sylvester who is having a bad day.

title: Party Boat
description: The Looney Builders build a party boat for Mac and Tosh when Tweety accidentally makes a mistake but doesn't ask for help.

title: Buzz In
description: Bizzy Buzzard's mom hires The Looney Builders to build her family a new nest. Bizzy wants to help but keeps getting in the way creating all sorts of problems for the crew.

title: Jelly Jam Jam
description: Ella helps Mei make some delicious jams using fresh produce from Lellobee City Farm.

title: Chinese New Year
description: The farm is decorated for Chinese New Year. A party is taking place!

title: Islands
description: Blippi wonders why don't islands float away?

title: Music is Everywhere
description: When music-lover Nia gets stranded before a big concert she's been waiting to see, Thomas brings the concert to her!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Roll Chickens, Roll!/Ramp Up, Up, And Away
description: Farmer MacBarm is hosting the Sunny Field Farm Chicken Roll, but the race gets off to a slow start when the chickens don't roll./Ranger Nat can't wait to see Pinecone's Comet, that is, until his telescope falls to the bottom of a cliff.

title: Nobody's Perfect
description: When Cheer makes some simple mistakes, she begins to lose confidence in her piloting skills and herself. The self-doubt becomes so severe, she decides to step away from her role as pilot of the Cloudseeker. But the Team needs her, the Whiffles need her, and she must regain her self-confidence so they can stop Bluster's latest nefarious scheme.

title: Animal sounds on the farm (I Hear With My Little Ear)
description: Ella and Rishi play a listening game. They hear expected sounds and an unexpected one! SLURP!

title: Backwards Day
description: It's Backwards Day! But Thomas misunderstands the game and accidentally delivers the wrong cargo to the wrong places.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Shake the Apple Tree
description: It's the end of the summer and the trees are full of delicious apples ready to be picked!

title: The Big Rumble
description: A family of comically raucous rocks moves in near a Whiffle garden and drives them to distraction with their ground-pounding games. Funshine gets the rocks to leave. But when he learns their ground-pounding creates new soil, he must convince them to come back.

title: Winter Football Soccer Song
description: Ella and friends take on the away team for a friendly game of three a side football on a snowy day.

title: Bibi's Do-Over
description: Everyone is ecstatic when Bibi, Batgirl, and Robin capture Toyman and his Do-Over remote - except for Bibi, who failed to stick the landing on a big jump. Unwilling to accept her failure, Bibi uses Toyman's Do-Over remote until she perfects her jump!

title: Takers Keepers/D-A-F-F-Y (song)/To Tell the Tooth
description: Takers Keepers: Daffy steals Taz's favorite toy but he learns you can't just take everything you want./To Tell the Tooth: When Bugs loses a baby tooth, Daffy tries to figure out how to scam the tooth fairy.

title: An UnbeLEAFable Day
description: While the trains are setting up for the Vicarstown Fall Festival, Thomas is feeling down about the end of summer and the changing weather.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Soup Up
description: As The Looney Builders help Petunia build a greenhouse, she can't wait for the veggies to grow and does everything she can to speed up the process.

title: Snowplow Struttin'
description: Thomas is thrilled -- Sir Topham Hatt has given him a snowplow in preparation for a big storm on the way, and the Number One Engine is ready to show off his skills! But when he is assigned to guide Diesel and Percy on their deliveries in case of snow, Thomas learns that he needs to use his plow responsibly for his friends and their tasks!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Get in Gear/Free-Wheelin' Ferris Wheel
description: Panic erupts in Pretty Big City when the big clock breaks and no one is able to tell what time it is./Zee is showing off his inventions at his rocket-powered show, including his latest creation, a rocket powered Ferris wheel.

title: Batcomputer for a Day
description: When Batcomputer shuts down for a system update, the other Batwheels must take over for her while aiding Batman in a battle against Harley Quinn.

title: Healthy Habits
description: A song that highlights what habits everyone should do daily in order to lead a healthy life - brushing their teeth, washing their hands, eating healthy foods and exercising. 'If you want a good day, do everything the healthy way, healthy is the way to be, with your friends at Lellobee'.

title: Planets
description: Three, two, one, Blast Off! The BlippiMobile becomes a spacecraft on this mission to find out which planets are in the solar system! Merry the Meteor is the perfect host as Blippi is escorted through space and receives a guided tour of all the planets and their positions from the sun.

title: Bedtime Routine
description: Jessica wants to be a big kid and get ready for bed all on her own, but she can't remember everything in her routine.

title: The Quest for the Rainbow Stone
description: A new bear named Togetherness is about to become an official Care Bear when Cheer accidentally breaks the magical stone needed to choose her color! The bears venture to a mystical cave full of puzzles and booby traps to find a new stone.

title: Yes Yes Bed Time
description: None of the animals want to go to bed. A cuddle from Ella is the only thing that makes them settle.

title: Return to Care-A-Lot
description: Bluster and his bad crowd invade Care-A-Lot, determined to steal the Care-O-Meter and stop the Care Bears' mission of caring and sharing. To foil his plan, the Bears must rely on an unlikely ally.

title: Time and Time Again/Does Your Tongue Hang Low (song)/May the Best Taz Win
description: Time and Time Again: The babies learn the importance of telling time./May the Best Taz Win: Lola learns she can't be the best at every sport.

title: Wheels on the Bus
description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

title: Race Track Race
description: The Looney Builders race against the clock to build Cecil Turtle a new racetrack. Daffy gets caught up in his own desire to race and changes part of the build.

title: Spin Out/Taz's Fridge (song)/Snow Day
description: Spinout: Taz learns a tough lesson. He shouldn't spin after eating too much candy./Snow Day: The babies experience their first snowfall.

title: Out of the Cheer Zone
description: Two mischievous Whiffle kids come to play with Dibble, forcing Cheer to put her important work on hold to manage them. When she finds her "managing kids" skills lacking and her important work in jeopardy, she uses her skills as a leader to get the kids working as a team to help her complete her work while having fun at the same time.

title: Earth Day
description: Ella and Bee demonstrate three things we can all do daily to help the earth - litter picking, composting and recycling. They will show us that every day can be an Earth Day. While Mei has planted a special "earth day" flower bed which the Lellobee City Farm friends gather around to celebrate earth day.

title: Off the Rails
description: Nia must get a huge earth ball from Whiff's Recycling Plant to Norramby Beach, but all the rail lines are blocked! When the bouncy ball rolls off Nia's flatcar and begins a wild odyssey across Sodor, she tries to control every bounce with all her friends' help. Nia learns to roll with the bounces and calls on an unlikely hero at sea to save the cargo!
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Hide and Sneak
description: Dibble is chosen as "It" in a Whiffle game of Hide-and-Seek. The game turns serious when Bluster traps the Bears inside the Cloudseeker. Dibble and Cheer must find the Whiffles and free her friends.

title: A Wish-Full Reunion
description: Mysterious flying hearts appear in Care-A-Lot and bring Wish Bear to the Silver Lining. She joins the Care Bears on a mission to bring a mystical mother bird's missing baby chicks home, and give a new home to an orphan bird.
